article.headline: NC A&amp,T 91, Md.-Eastern Shore 66
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Marc Hill led five Aggies in double-figures as North Carolina A&T routed Maryland-Eastern Shore 91-66 on Saturday for their fifth straight win. Adrian Powell had 15 points while Austin Witter, Nic Simpson, and R.J. Buck all added 11 for North Carolina A&T. Hill was 7 of 11 from the field and made all four of his 3-point attempts for the Aggies. North Carolina A&T (10-12, 5-2 MEAC) opened the game on a 20-6 run and expanded that lead to 42-17, with 4:31 left in the first half. The Aggies took a 49-26 lead into halftime and outscored the Hawks 42-40 in the second half. Percy Woods led Maryland-Eastern Shore (4-15, 1-5) with 16 but the Hawks shot just 34.9 percent (22 of 63) from the field. The Aggies were 29 of 62 from the floor. North Carolina A&T has won six of its last seven games after losing eight straight.
